title: Cross adds to fall cross country highlights
text:
Cross adds to fall cross country highlights Brian McCallum , FLORIDA TODAY 1:04 p.m. EDT October 4, 2015 Steven Cross won the FSU Invitational elite race on Saturday in Tallahassee. (Photo: Craig Bailey/FLORIDA TODAY) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Merritt Island senior Steven Cross added to his 2015 resume on Saturday with a win in the boys elite race at the FSU Invitational in Tallahassee, completing the 5,000-meter course in 15:21.10. Trevor Kattenberg of Satellite placed 17th individually of the 259 runners, in 15:57.00. 
The Satellite boys placed fourth, the highest team finish from Brevard County, averaging a 16:21. Egan Kattenberg was 26th, at 16:07.40. John Cacciatore was 37th (16:13.90) 
Shelby Smith of Holy Trinity placed 17th (18:45.20) among the girls. Sydney Smith placed 31st, in 19:20.90, and Lana Rukab of Satellite 48th (19:50.70). 
Holy Trinityâ€™s girls were 11th, with an average 19:57, and Satellite was 14th (20:18). 
Mason Jones of Titusville won the boys select race, with a 16:06.60. Amanda Beach won the girls select (18:53.90).
